  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC) has a relatively bad prognosis whereas there is no
      standard regimen. Some data showed that platins could improve the efficacy of advance TNBC.
      In this trial, it is the hypothesis that TP (docetaxel plus carboplatin) has a better
      efficacy than EC-T (epirubicin plus cyclophosphamide followed by docetaxel).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
